$ALMU Bears went from &quot;it&#39;s a scam&quot; to &quot;I&#39;m just concerned for you guys.&quot;
NVDA is throwing billions at $LITE  and $COHR because the infrastructure needs it. The incumbents benefit today, but scaling pure InP manufacturing is a legitimate challenge because of expensive substrates, limited supply, and small wafer sizes.
The industry needs a path to higher-volume manufacturing. That&#39;s the debate. Not the fake concern trolling.

